					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">bmac6502 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">while the CPUs' execution, address registers, etc. may lead it to work on addresses up to $BFFF, the external address lines will never generate a value higher than $2FFF</div>
<br />$4000-$FFFF is mirrored down to $0000-$3FFF internally in the PPU. The mirroring of $3000-$3EFF down to $2000-$2EFF is done by the cartridge, but $3000-$3FFF never gets put on the PPU address bus during rendering. The only way that $3000-$3EFF gets put on the PPU address bus is if the CPU is using CPU $2006/$2007 writes. I don't know for sure whether access to PPU $3F00-$3FFF through CPU $2006/$2007 with rendering turned off gets put on the PPU address bus; if it does, /RD and /WR don't go low.</div>

